    <div class="news-card" date="1532355097172">
      <p><b>JUL 23</b></p>
      <p>Introducing Offline Mode for Docs!</p><br>
      <p>This was the most requested feature for Docs. You can now selectively make documents available offline.</p><br>
      <p><span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-fw fa-lock"></i></span> Offline documents will be stored encrypted on your device, and will be sync'ed both ways with all your devices when you launch Cryptee with internet connection.</p><br>
      <p><span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-fw fa-bolt"></i></span> Best part of it all is that if you have a document stored offline on your device, they will now load almost instantly when you click on them, and will be sync'ed in the background once saved.</p><br>
      <p><span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-fw fa-bug"></i></span> Due to the many thousands of lines of code required to make this feature, there may still be a few tiny bugs left here and there. Please reach out if you find anything using the bug report button (<span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-fw fa-bug"></i></span>) on the top left corner of Docs.</p>
    </div>


